result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Tedama A Taylor in court.  Attorney Jeff Allen Schwarz in court for Tedama A Taylor.  Attorney Dennis Murphy in court on behalf of Alexander James Geocaris for State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for a scheduling conference. Defense counsel has  received discovery and no offer from the state.  Defense requests a status date. Court grants request. Case remains calendared in Branch 11.
Status conference scheduled for November 10, 2022 at 02:30 pm.

Defendant Tedama A Taylor in court with Attorney Jeff Allen Schwarz; both appear by video.  Abby Rockendorf appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin.  
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: West Allis Officer R. Seghers. State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 11.  Scheduling conference scheduled for September 27, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with AMD, KSH, TTJ. 
No Weapons Order, signed and filed.

Defendant Tedama A Taylor in court with attorney Colleen A Taylor.  Stephanie Krueger appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant given a copy of complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause to hold defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Reserve Judge John Franke.  Case is adjourned for preliminary hearing in Branch PE.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for August 4, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Tedama A Taylor not in court.  Katrina Amy Voge appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant called and informed the court that she might have COVID. 
Defendant failing to appear, court ordered arrest warrant issued but STAYED issuance until 7/18/2022, at 1:30 p.m. If she fails to appear at her next court appearance a WARRANT will be issued.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for July 18, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Summons mailed.  Defendant ordered into room 221 Safety Building on 6-29-2022 @1:30p
